<AbstractNarration>Two related projects are designed to advance the robotic tools and techniques for effective subterranean rescue while providing a quality research experience for undergraduates at Berea College.  The students will work in interdisciplinary cooperative learning groups with the research teams at the Industry/University Cooperative Research Center for Safety, Security and Rescue.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;The students will also develop, analyze and simulate algorithms for dispersing a collective team of Scout robots in an unknown environment using non-centrally controlled solutions.  &lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
